<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,719,158,185]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
Key to the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gussone ex Lojacono" authorityYear="1903" box="[430,640,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aeolica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[430,640,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">Centaurea aeolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="21" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,219,443]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
1. Basal leaves usually lyrate, with lacinia apex obtuse to rounded, phyllaries pale brown with blackish apex, with 1 to 2–5 teeth..... ....................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beguinot" authorityYear="1905" baseAuthorityName="Fiori &amp; Beguinot" box="[1316,1451,248,270]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pandataria">
<emphasis box="[1316,1451,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">C. pandataria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,219,443]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="21">– Basal leaves 1–2-pinnatisect, never lyrate, with lacinia apex acute, phyllaries whitish to straw-coloured, with 7–15 teeth or fimbriae...............................................................................................................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,219,443]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
2. Tomentum greenish-grey, leaves 1–2-pinnatisect, with laciniae loosely inserted, phyllaries 7-nerved, appendages denticulate with teeth 
<quantity box="[263,390,363,385]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="0.175" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.05">0.05–0.3 mm</quantity>
long....................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gussone ex Lojacono" authorityYear="1903" box="[1352,1451,363,385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aeolica">
<emphasis box="[1352,1451,363,385]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">C. aeolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,219,443]" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
<keyLead pageId="12" pageNumber="21">
– Tomentum whitish-grey, leaves 1-pinnatisect (rarely 2-pinnatisect), with laciniae densely inserted, phyllaries 5-nerved, appendages fimbriate with fimbriae up to 
<quantity box="[495,568,421,443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long ................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1451,421,442]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="12" pageNumber="21" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phalacrica">
<emphasis box="[1319,1451,421,442]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="21">C. phalacrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
